Russia’s RTS Stock-Index Futures Fall 0.2% at Start of Trading

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-03-31T15:08:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/russia-s-rts-stock-index-futures-fall-0-2-at-start-of-trading.html
Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
expiring in June fell 0.2 percent to 198,840 by 11:03 a.m. in
 New York .  Contracts on OAO Sberbank, Russia’s largest lender, dropped
0.1 percent, while contracts on OAO Gazprom, the natural-gas
export monopoly, also slid 0.1 percent. Contracts on OAO Lukoil,
the country’s second-biggest oil producer, declined 0.2 percent.
The Market Vectors Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that holds
Russian shares, retreated 0.1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
 hpavliva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
